  "text": "Previous work in our group demonstrated that human cathelicidin LL-37 is very sensitive to proteases from E. histolytica, being degraded in just one hour [CITATION_1] . We decided to test the stability of pro-prophenin 2 by Western blot of the propeptide after 1, 2, and 4 h of interaction with T. vaginalis, using the anti-FLAG M2 antibody. We detected the presence of proprophenin 2 in all lanes (Figure 6) , even in samples that were not treated with the cysteine proteinase inhibitor E64; although after 4 h interaction, without E-64, the signal was very weak (lane 3).",
